column3: str
Rral Soj has a new order of business to discuss.

Rral Soj has tasked you with crafting tortilla presses for Aunt Tii's Tacos.

※Minimum collectability rating for this delivery is 210. Delivering items with a rating of 430 or more will earn greater rewards.

You deliver the tortilla presses to Rral Soj. Aunt Tii soon arrives to pick them up, and is pleased to see her bulk order was finished in time─no thanks to Papawni, unfortunately, who was so fixated on crafting a flawless press, that she only managed to make a single one. It seems Rral Soj will still need your help for now.
Deliver the tortilla presses to Rral Soj.
I never realized it would warm my heart so, to be thanked directly by a patron... It's a wonderful feeling!
Glad you're here, <Split(<Highlight>ObjectParameter(1)</Highlight>, ,1)/>.
Thanks to our last client, word of our efficiency seems to have spread, and a new bulk order has come in. I trust I can still count on your help?
So, what's the request this time?
...A large order o' tortilla presses for Aunt Tii's.
Er...who's that?
What? You've never heard o' Aunt Tii's Tacos? It's one o' the most popular taco places in the city.
I see... But are tortilla presses normally ordered in bulk? Surely her stock didn't break all at once...?

This is somethin' of a special case. Seems the manufactory in charge o' Tii's tortilla production's havin' a complete overhaul, and everythin' needs replaced─spares included. She wants us to prepare as many presses as possible.
<Split(<Highlight>ObjectParameter(1)</Highlight>, ,1)/>, I'd like you to make six o' 'em. Papawni and I'll handle the remainder.
Tii entrusted this order to my shop 'cause she has faith we'll get the job done in a timely fashion. Let's show her what we're made of.
You've got it! I'll do my best to make sure she leaves just as satisfied as our last customer!
As I understand, the most crucial factor is to ensure each tortilla is pressed to a uniform size... This may require some metalworking wizardry!
I'll be hard at work craftin' my share o' presses when I get a spare moment from tendin' the shop. Soon as you have your share ready, just say the word.
Ah, finished already, have you? Aunt Tii is sure to be satisfied with this handiwork.

Ah, finished already, have you? This has jus' the right amount o' weightiness to it, an' the surfaces look perfectly flat. I daresay Tii will steal whatever competition is left with the tortillas she makes from these.
Everyone, meet Tii. Tii, meet the team.

Hello, hello! I'm Tiisol, the proud owner of Aunt Tii's Tacos! It's lovely to meet you all. Your lightning-fast work with the presses is an absolute <Emphasis>godssend</Emphasis>─I can't thank you enough!

We'd been using only hardwood presses at the manufactory till now, but I can't tell you how many times I've had to order replacements. The things seem to break at the slightest bit of force! Having metal presses will be a huge relief.
I promise you these can take a beatin', and then some.
Oh, I don't doubt it! And, seeing as you've proven yourself a woman of your word, you'll be the first person I come to for my cooking supplies from now on!

Now then, I must be getting these presses to the manufactory, so I'll excuse myself here. Do be sure to visit my store next chance you get─would be a shame if you didn't get a taste of the tortillas you had a hand in making!
We'd never have been able to fulfill the order in time if not for you, <Split(<Highlight>ObjectParameter(1)</Highlight>, ,1)/>. My thanks.
<Split(<Highlight>ObjectParameter(1)</Highlight>, ,1)/>, Mistress Rral Soj... I am so, so sorry. Once again, I was too slow. I only managed to prepare a single press...
Papawni. You put your heart into your work. I can see that.

But if you're gonna continue to work here, you need to come to grips with the stipulations o' the job. Truth be told, I need you outputtin' the same amount as <Split(<Highlight>ObjectParameter(1)</Highlight>, ,1)/> here.
I've been watchin' you work. You spend far too much time devotin' your attention to a single item.
I-I'm sorry! I was so thrilled to see my efforts appreciated before, I thought that if I put my all into these presses as well, Mistress Tiisol would be overjoyed...
I wanted to make them flawless and easy to maintain, and in the process...I completely lost track of the time.
I admire that you're trying to make the best product possible, but sometimes a customer only wants a tool that works─and they want it quick. Try to keep that in mind next time.
<Split(<Highlight>ObjectParameter(1)</Highlight>, ,1)/>, looks like you're not rid of me yet. I can't rely on your help forever, but for now, please continue to lend us your expertise.
Rral Soj is delighted with your efforts. She now considers you a <UIForeground>F201F4</UIForeground><UIGlow>F201F5</UIGlow>Marvelous Metalworker<UIGlow>01</UIGlow><UIForeground>01</UIForeground>!
The next request will be available from Rral Soj upon reaching level 95 as a blacksmith, armorer, or goldsmith.
